Individual Record: 21-11

#2: 1-1

#3: 20-10

Prior to Arizona

Is the all-time individual career wins leader with 39 at Missouri State

Played in all 28 matches as a junior, posting a 23-5 record in the No. 2 flight

Her 23 wins was the most in a single-season in program history with a single pair

Became a part of the first MSU pair to eclipse 20 wins in a season

Played 15 matches as a sophomore at MSU, posting a 12-3 record in the No. 2 spot

Her 12 wins as a was the most in a single-season in program history

Recorded two wins over ranked opponents defeating Arizona (March 3) and LSU (March 23)

Appeared in all 12 matches as a true freshman at Missouri State in 2020, going 4-5 in the No. 3 pair, 0-2 in the second flight and 0-1 at the four spot

Spent most of her high school career as the No. 1 pair, earning rookie of the year honors in the program’s inaugural season in spring 2017

Team MVP as a junior on a club that posted an unbeaten record and advanced to the Arizona Division I Final Four

Top-eight finisher at the Arizona State Pairs Tournament in 2018

Played setter and right side for the Sandra Day O’Connor High indoor team
